HEADWORD: Questionist
<hw>Ques"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A questioner; an
inquirer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eng. Univ.)</fld> <def>A candidate for honors or
degrees who is near the time of his examination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Questionless</ent>⟦br⟧
